Brazil to Spend $14 Billion on World Cup Investments, Sports Minister Says

-- B y   A n d r e   S o l i a n i
-- 
2011-07-21T14:47:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-21/brazil-to-spend-14-billion-on-world-cup-investments-sports-minister-says.html
Brazil ’s government plans to spend
$14 billion on infrastructure for the 2014 soccer  World Cup , the
country’s sports minister Orlando Silva said in a telephone
conference call.   The World Cup will generate 700,000 new jobs, Silva said.
The 12 stadiums for the tournament will be ready the end of
2013, he added.  To contact the reporter on this story:
